                <text type="case">
                                <body>
                                                <p><hi rend="initialcap">C</hi>ASE.—<name type="person">Corporal W. W. Barlow</name>, <name type="organization">Co. B, 1st Maine
                                                                Cavalry</name>, aged 23 years, was wounded at <name type="battle">Dinwiddie
                                                                                Court-house, Virginia</name>, <date type="injury" when="1865-03-31">March 31st, 1865</date>, by a
                                                  conoidal musket ball, which caused a compound
                                                  fracture of outer table of the <hi rend="italic">os frontis</hi>, left
                                                  side, with compound comminution of inner table. He
                                                  was admitted into the <name type="hospital">Cavalry Corps Hospital</name> at
                                                                <name type="place">City Point, Virginia</name>, on <date type="admit" when="1865-04-01">the following day</date>, and
                                                                transferred on <date type="transfer" when="1865-04-04">April 4th</date> to Washington, per
                                                                <name type="hospital">hospital steamer Thomas Powell</name>, entering <name type="hospital" key="165">Mount Pleasant Hospital</name> on <date type="transfer" when="1865-04-04">the same day</date>. The case
                                                                progressed favorably until the morning of <date type="injury" when="1865-04-07">the 7th</date>,
                                                  when the patient had convulsions, followed by
                                                  intense headache. The fractured portion of the
                                                  outer table was <date type="operation" when="1865-04-07">then</date> removed. On <date type="operation" when="1865-04-08">the following day</date>
                                                  ether and chloroform was administered, and
                                                                <name type="person" key="245">Assistant Surgeon H. Allen</name>, <name type="organization" key="190">U. S. A.</name>, removed two
                                                  large pieces of the inner table through the
                                                  opening which had been enlarged by the trephine.
                                                  Small fragments of bone came away from time to
                                                  time, but the case progressed favorably, and on
                                                  the <date type="servicedischarge" when="1865-06-15">June 15th, 1865</date>, the patient was discharged
                                                  from the service and pensioned. His disability is
                                                  total. </p>
                                                
